Actually, using the `FolioReaderKit 1.4.0` pod, you can&#39;t.

On the [1.4.0 release podspec][1], it depends explicitly on RealmSwift 3.13.1:


    &quot;RealmSwift&quot;: [
      &quot;3.13.1&quot;
    ]

On the other hand, `RealmSwift 3.13.1` [depends][2] on the same version of Realm:

    &quot;dependencies&quot;: {
      &quot;Realm&quot;: [
        &quot;= 3.13.1&quot;
      ]
    }

So you can&#39;t just manually update the versions.

The only way you can update this is creating a local copy of `FolioReaderKit` and manually modifying its `podspec` file, but it probably has some reason to fix the pod dependency version, so it is likely to crash.

  [1]: https://github.com/CocoaPods/Specs/blob/master/Specs/2/c/a/FolioReaderKit/1.4.0/FolioReaderKit.podspec.json
  [2]: https://github.com/CocoaPods/Specs/blob/master/Specs/9/4/5/RealmSwift/3.13.1/RealmSwift.podspec.json

